summary:
10. The Committee will intensify efforts to promote full implementation of resolution 1540 (2004) through its Programme of Work, which includes compilation of information, outreach, dialogue, assistance, and cooperation.

11. To achieve this, the Committee will: 
(a) continue dialogue with States on implementation actions and technical assistance;
(b) organize outreach events at regional, subregional, and national levels;
(c) strengthen its role in facilitating technical assistance;
(d) engage with States and organizations to promote sharing of experience and lessons learned;
(e) provide opportunities for interaction with interested States and organizations.

12. Cooperation between the 1540 Committee and other Security Council Committees (established pursuant to resolutions 1267 (1999) and 1373 (2001)) is to be enhanced.

13. The Committee is urged to encourage and utilize voluntary financial contributions to assist States in implementing resolution 1540 (2004) and to explore options for existing funding mechanisms.

14. The Committee will submit a report to the Security Council by 24 April 2011 on compliance with resolution 1540 (2004).

15. The Security Council will remain seized of the matter.
